# SWT dashboard live event stream (per-session JSONL emitted by the CLI;
# session-local state, not project artifact).
#
# Also ignore `.swt-planning/`: the dashboard's Init flow creates
# `.swt-planning/PROJECT.md` + `STATE.md` in the daemon's cwd, which during
# local development of SWT itself is the source repo root. SWT v3 development
# uses `.vbw-planning/` (VBW-driven), so `.swt-planning/` here is always
# dev-test detritus and should never enter git. When SWT-on-SWT dogfooding
# lands, this entry needs revisiting.
.swt-planning/
# Exception: test-utils fixtures (v2-baseline for the migration boot-clean
# test + future v3-baseline parity recordings) are intentional, committed
# golden artefacts. Plan 06-04 T1 (REQ-19).
!packages/test-utils/golden/**/.swt-planning/
!packages/test-utils/golden/**/.swt-planning/**

# Changesets internals
.changeset/.changes-*/

# Local research artefact (kept out of git unless intentionally added)
compass_artifact_*.md

# Local working copy of VBW (out of git; not part of SWT)
vibe-better-with-claude-code-vbw-main/

# Non-production scratch / experiment files (anywhere in the tree, all
# current and future contents). Keep out of git so the repo stays
# focused on shippable code.
non_production_files/

# --- VBW planning state (fully local as of 2026-05-12) ---
#
# `.vbw-planning/` is **fully gitignored** — planning artifacts
# (PROJECT.md, REQUIREMENTS.md, ROADMAP.md, STATE.md, phase plans,
# summaries, research, and the VBW runtime state) are LOCAL ONLY.
# Earlier policy tracked them on v3-foundation; the 2026-05-12 main-
# only pivot retired that branch and the workspace is now treated as
# Claude Code session scratch, not a shared planning surface.
#
# Historical commits still resolve to the previously-tracked content
# via git's blob history — only the working-tree visibility changes.
# Public commit messages and CHANGELOG entries reference plan
# numbering (PR-NN) which stays meaningful; the plan files themselves
# stay on the local machine of whoever's driving the session.
#
# NOTE: written as `.vbw-planning/*` (not `.vbw-planning/`) so git still
# descends into the directory and honors per-subpath negation rules below
# (Phase 04 plan 04-01 needs to track .vbw-planning/upstream-prompt-snapshots/).
# A trailing-slash directory ignore makes the dir itself untracked and
# blocks any !-prefixed re-inclusion of children. See the negation block
# at the bottom of this file.
.vbw-planning/*

# TDD3 working doc (transposition spec — never committed)
TDD3.md

# Non-production assets (porter source-of-truth, dev scratch). Purged from history.
/a_non_production_files/

# Vendored VBW methodology scripts — regenerated by
# scripts/internal/port-from-vbw.sh from
# a_non_production_files/vibe-better-with-claude-code-vbw-main/scripts/.
# Not tracked in git; the porter is the single source of truth.
scripts/*
# Carve out the porter itself (SWT-owned automation, not VBW asset).
!scripts/lib/
scripts/lib/*
!scripts/internal/
!scripts/internal/port-from-vbw.sh
# Carve out SWT-owned scripts (pre-port, not VBW assets).
!scripts/bump-version.sh
!scripts/check-bundle-size.mjs
!scripts/check-offline.mjs
!scripts/check-tarball-shape.mjs
# Phase 18 plan 02-01 (G-02): nested .npmignore — npm 11 ignores root .npmignore
# when files[] lists a directory, so the carve-out for scripts/internal/ and
# scripts/.port-rewrites.json MUST live inside scripts/ to take effect.
!scripts/.npmignore
!scripts/docs-gen.ts
# Phase 17 plan 01-01 T1: spawn-snapshot determinism tool (gates Provider-isolation invariant D2).
!scripts/spawn-snapshot.ts
!scripts/public-benchmark.mjs
!scripts/record-cassette.mjs
# Phase 2 / Plan 02-01 (G-R3): developer-local rate-card refresh.
!scripts/refresh-rate-card.mjs
!scripts/record-cassette-scenarios/
!scripts/record-cassette-scenarios/*.mjs
!scripts/stub-test-chaos.mjs
!scripts/stub-test-provider-matrix.mjs
!scripts/stub-test-regression.mjs
!scripts/verify-install.sh
# Carve out Phase 02 SWT-side rewrites of §6.3 scripts (Pi-substrate-aware
# replacements for Claude-Code-specific VBW originals). The porter's cp -n
# preserves these on re-run, but they need to be tracked so they ship with
# the npm tarball and arrive in fresh clones.
!scripts/lib/swt-session-state.sh
!scripts/lib/swt-team-state.sh
!scripts/agent-pid-tracker.sh
!scripts/agent-start.sh
!scripts/agent-stop.sh
!scripts/agent-spawn-guard.sh
!scripts/clean-stale-teams.sh
# Milestone-23 init-wizard scripts: VBW-authored but SWT product code in
# packages/core/src/scaffold/ shells out to them via initProject(). They must
# ship with the npm tarball + be present in CI. alpha.44 failed at the Test
# step because these scripts were absent on the GitHub Actions runner. Tracking
# them here follows the same pattern as the agent-state scripts above (SWT-side
# rewrites of VBW originals — Pi-substrate-aware).
!scripts/planning-git.sh
!scripts/detect-stack.sh
!scripts/bootstrap/
!scripts/bootstrap/*.sh
!scripts/tmux-watchdog.sh
!scripts/lease-lock.sh
!scripts/hook-wrapper.sh
!scripts/cache-nuke.sh
!scripts/install-hooks.sh
!scripts/ensure-plugin-root-link.sh
!scripts/compaction-instructions.sh
!scripts/post-compact.sh
!scripts/lib/swt-cache-key.sh
!scripts/lib/swt-config-root.sh
!scripts/lib/swt-target-root.sh
# Phase 04 plan 04-04: SWT-side rewrite (4-line layout + SWT naming + metrics wiring).
!scripts/swt-statusline.sh
# Phase 04 plan 04-01 T5: cook PreToolUse/PostToolUse hook publisher.
!scripts/hooks/
!scripts/hooks/cook-event-publisher.sh

# Phase 02 closure manifest — tracks status of §6.3 rewrites for the porter.
!scripts/.port-rewrites.json
# Phase 06 plan 06-05 T2: reproducible bulk-sed bats-fixture rename.
!scripts/bulk-sed-bats-rename.sh
# Phase 04 plan 04-01 T1: SWT-owned cook command contract test
# (renamed from the never-carved-out scripts/verify-vibe.sh).
!scripts/verify-cook.sh
# alpha.13: promote to SWT-owned because the published CLI bundle invokes
# them at runtime (verify.ts:454 → prepare-reverification.sh; runtime's
# Bash PreToolUse hook → bash-guard.sh). Both pull in transitive deps —
# uat-utils.sh and lib/active-agent-state.sh — so the full closure ships.
# Without these carve-outs the release CI runs from a fresh clone where
# they don't exist, so they never made it into the npm tarball.
!scripts/bash-guard.sh
!scripts/prepare-reverification.sh
!scripts/uat-utils.sh
!scripts/lib/active-agent-state.sh
# Phase 04 plan 04-01 T1: upstream-prompt-drift audit script + fixture-driven
# test seam. Both are SWT-owned (not VBW-vendored), so they need explicit
# carve-outs to escape the `scripts/*` directory ignore above.
!scripts/audit-upstream-prompts.sh
!scripts/test-audit-upstream-prompts.sh

# Phase 06 plan 06-01: Lark→TS apply_patch parser generator + fixture-capture
# helper. SWT-owned (not VBW-vendored); the generator re-runs in CI for
# grammar drift detection so it MUST be tracked. Per-file carve-outs match
# the per-file convention used above.
!scripts/codegen/
!scripts/codegen/apply-patch-from-lark.ts
!scripts/codegen/capture-apply-patch-fixtures.ts

# Phase 04 plan 04-01: upstream-prompt-drift baselines are tracked even though
# the rest of .vbw-planning/ is local-only. Baselines are the audit's source of
# truth and must survive across clones for the cron job to compare against.
# Narrowly carve out ONLY the snapshots subtree — STATE.md, ROADMAP.md, plans,
# etc. remain local-only per the directory-wide .vbw-planning/ ignore.
!.vbw-planning/upstream-prompt-snapshots/
!.vbw-planning/upstream-prompt-snapshots/**
